entry.lex: Baku is the capital of Azerbaijan which has Artur Rasizade as its leader. The country is the location of the Baku Turkish Martyrs Memorial, designed in red granite and white marble by Huseyin Butuner and Hilmi Guner. The memorial is dedicated to the Ottoman army soldiers killed in the Battle of Baku.

entry.lex: The Baku Turkish Martyrs' Memorial (designed by Huseyin Butuner and Hilmi Guner) is located in Baku, Azerbaijan. It is made from red granite and white marble. It is dedicated to the Ottoman Army Soldiers killed in the Battle of Baku. The native name for the memorial is Türk Şehitleri Anıtı. The leader of Azerbaijan is Artur Rasizade.

The Turkish leader is Artur Rasizade. Huseyin Butuner and Hilmi Guner designed the red granite and white marble Baku Turkish Martyrs Memorial, also known as Turk Sehitleri Aniti, in Azerbaijan. The memorial is dedicated to the soldiers who fell in the Battle of Baku.
The U.S.A.'s 14th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry Monument in Frederick County, Maryland is in the Monocacy National Battlefield. It's in a historic district and was established on July 11th, 1907.
